    <h3>Origin of Pizza</h3>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Origins:</strong> Pizza traces back to ancient civilizations like Greeks, Egyptians, and Romans.</li>
        <li><strong>Ancient Flatbreads:</strong> Greeks made flatbreads; Egyptians had flatbreads with herbs and spices.</li>
        <li><strong>Roman Influence:</strong> Romans made flatbreads with toppings like cheese and honey.</li>
        <li><strong>Italian Roots:</strong> Modern pizza originated in Naples, Italy, with toppings like tomatoes and cheese.</li>
        <li><strong>Pizza Margherita:</strong> Created in honor of Queen Margherita, featuring tomatoes, mozzarella, and basil.</li>
        <li><strong>Global Popularity:</strong> Pizza spread globally, evolving into various styles and becoming a beloved dish worldwide.</li>
        <li><strong>Continued Evolution:</strong> Today, pizza remains popular, with countless variations and styles reflecting diverse culinary preferences.</li>
    </ul>
